"numeric field" => "Zahl",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Provides a one-line field for numeric input only.  Prepend or append values may be alphanumeric.\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>samerow,size,prepend,append,decimals,dec_point,thousands</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Example: 0,60,,hours\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[samerow]</strong> will display the next field or checkbox in the same row if a 1 is specified;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[size]</strong> is the visible size of the field in characters;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[prepend]</strong> is text that will be displayed before the field;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[append]</strong> is text that will be displayed just after the field;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[decimals]</strong> sets the number of decimal places;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[dec_point]</strong> sets the separator for the decimal point (decimals must also be set). Use c for comma and s for space;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[thousands]</strong> sets the thousands separator. Use c for comma and s for space. Setting only commas will result in no decimals \n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tand commas as the thousands seprator;<br/><br/>\n\t\t\t\t<dd>multiple options must appear in the order specified, separated by commas.\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl> \t\t\t\t<dt>Funktion: Es wird ein einzeiliges Feld für die Eingabe von Zahlen erstellt.. Vorangestellte oder angehängte Werte können alphanumerisch sein. \t\t\t\t<dt>Benutzung: <strong>samerow,size,prepend,append,decimals,dec_point,thousands</strong> \t\t\t\t<dt>Beispiel: 0,60,,Stunden \t\t\t\t<dt>Beschreibung: \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[samerow]</strong> zeigt das nächste Feld oder die nächste Checkbox in der gleichen Zeile, wenn eine 1 angegeben wird; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[size]</strong> ist die sichtbare Grösse des Feldes in Zeichen; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[prepend]</strong> ist ein Text, der vor dem Feld angezeigt wird; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[append]</strong> ist ein Text, der just nach dem Feld angezeigt wird; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[decimals]</strong> legt fest, wieviele Nachkommastellen angezeigt werden; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[dec_point]</strong> Legt das Nachkommastellen-Trennzeichen fest (ein Eintrag für Nachkommastellen muss vorgenommen werden). Benutze c für Komma und s für Leerzeichen; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[thousands]</strong> Legt das Tausendertrennzeichen fest. Benutze c für Komma und s für Leerzeichen. Werden nur Kommata angegeben, werden keine Nachkommastellen und dafür Kommata als Tausendertrennzeichen angezeigt;<br/><br/> \t\t\t\t<dd>Multiple Optionen müssen in der vorgegebenen Reihenfolge angegeben werden, getrennt durch Kommata. \t\t\t\t</dl>",
"currency amount" => "Währungsbetrag",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Provides a one-line field for numeric input only.  Prepend or append values may be alphanumeric.\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>samerow,size,prepend,append,locale,symbol,first</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Example: 0,60,,per item\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[samerow]</strong> will display the next field or checkbox in the same row if a 1 is specified;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[size]</strong> is the visible size of the field in characters;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[prepend]</strong> is text that will be displayed before the field;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[append]</strong> is text that will be displayed just after the field;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[locale]</strong> set locale for currency formatting, for example en_US or en_US.UTF-8 or en_US.ISO-8559-1 (default=en_US);\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[currency]</strong> The 3-letter ISO 4217 currency code indicating the currency to use (default=USD);\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[symbol]</strong> i for international symbol, n for local (default=n);\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[all_symbol]</strong> set to 1 to show symbol for every item (default only shows currency symbol on first item in a list) ;\n\t\t\t\t<br/><br/>\n\t\t\t\t<dd>multiple options must appear in the order specified, separated by commas.\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl> \t\t\t\t<dt>Funktion: Es wird ein einzeiliges Feld für die Eingabe von Zahlen erstellt. Vorangestellte oder angehängte Werte können alphanumerisch sein. \t\t\t\t<dt>Benutzung: <strong>samerow,size,prepend,append,locale,symbol,first</strong> \t\t\t\t<dt>Beispiel: 0,60,,pro Eintrag \t\t\t\t<dt>Beschreibung: \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[samerow]</strong> zeigt das nächste Feld oder die nächste Checkbox in der gleichen Zeile, wenn eine 1 angegeben wird; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[size]</strong> ist die sichtbare Grösse des Feldes in Zeichen; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[prepend]</strong> ist ein Text, der vor dem Feld angezeigt wird; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[append]</strong> ist ein Text, der just nach dem Feld angezeigt wird; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[locale]</strong> Lokalisierung für Währungsformate, z.B. en_US oder en_US.UTF-8 oder en_US.ISO-8559-1 (standard=en_US); \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[currency]</strong> Der drei Zeichen lange ISO 4217 Währungscode, der die Währung vorgibt (standard=USD); \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[symbol]</strong> i für das internationale Symbol, n für lokal (standard=n); \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[all_symbol]</strong> Trage 1 ein, damit jeder Eintrag mit dem Symbol versehen wird (satndardmäßig wird das Währungssymbol nur beim ersten Eintrag der Liste angezeigt) ; \t\t\t\t<br/><br/> \t\t\t\t<dd>Multiple Optionen müssen in der vorgegebenen Reihenfolge angegeben werden, getrennt durch Kommata. \t\t\t\t</dl>",
"drop down" => "Auswahlliste",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows users to select only from a specified set of options in a drop-down bar.\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>list_of_items</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Example: yes,no\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[list_of_items]</strong> is the list of all values you want in the drop-down, separated by commas;\n\t\t\t\t<dd>if you wish to specify a default value other than the first item, enter the value twice, consecutively, and it will appear once in the list as the default selection.\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl> \t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows users to select only from a specified set of options in a drop-down bar. \t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>list_of_items</strong> \t\t\t\t<dt>Example: yes,no \t\t\t\t<dt>Description: \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[list_of_items]</strong> is the list of all values you want in the drop-down, separated by commas; \t\t\t\t<dd>if you wish to specify a default value other than the first item, enter the value twice, consecutively, and it will appear once in the list as the default selection. \t\t\t\t</dl>",
"drop down with other textfield" => "Listenfeld mit einem Textfeld verknüpft",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows users to select from a specified set of options in a drop-down bar, or provide an alternate selection in a one-line text field.\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>list_of_items</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Example: yes,no\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[list_of_items]</strong> is the list of all values you want in the drop-down, separated by commas;\n\t\t\t\t<dd>if you wish to specify a default value other than the first item, enter the value twice, consecutively, and it will appear once in the list as the default selection.\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl> \t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows users to select from a specified set of options in a drop-down bar, or provide an alternate selection in a one-line text field. \t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>list_of_items</strong> \t\t\t\t<dt>Example: yes,no \t\t\t\t<dt>Description: \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[list_of_items]</strong> is the list of all values you want in the drop-down, separated by commas; \t\t\t\t<dd>if you wish to specify a default value other than the first item, enter the value twice, consecutively, and it will appear once in the list as the default selection. \t\t\t\t</dl>",
"radio buttons" => "Radiobuttons",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Provides a multiple-choice-style set of options from which a user may only choose one.\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>list_of_items</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Example: yes,no\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[list of items]</strong> is the list of all values you want in the set, separated by commas;\n\t\t\t\t<dd>if you wish to specify a default value other than the first item, enter the value twice, consecutively, and it will appear as the one selected.\n\t\t\t\t<dd>If first option is &lt;br&gt;, options will be separated with a carriage return\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Funktion: Stellt eine Anzahl von Optionen mit multipler Auswahlmöglichkeit, von denen der Benutzer nur eine wählen darf.\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Benutzung: <strong>Liste_der_Optionent</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Beispiel: ja,nein\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Beschreibung:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[Liste der Optionen]</strong> ist die Liste von allen Werten, die in der Auswahl erscheinen sollen, getrennt durch Kommata;\n\t\t\t\t<dd>wenn ein anderer als der zuerst angegebene Wert als Standard festgelegt werden soll, trage den Wert zweimal hintereinander ein, und es wird derjenige sein, der zuerst gewählt ist.\n\t\t\t\t<dd>Wenn die erste Option &lt;br&gt; ist, werden alle Optionen mit einem Zeilenumbruch getrennt\n\t\t\t\t</dl>",
"user selector" => "Nutzerauswahl",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows a selection from a specified list of usernames.\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>auto-assign,email_notify</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Example: 1,1\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[auto-assign]</strong> will auto-assign the creator of the item if set to 1, or will set the selection to the user who last modified the item if set to 2, or will give the choice between all the users for other values;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[email_notify]</strong> will send an email to the assigned user when the item is saved;\n\t\t\t\t<dd>multiple options must appear in the order specified, separated by commas.\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl> \t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows a selection from a specified list of usernames. \t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>auto-assign,email_notify</strong> \t\t\t\t<dt>Example: 1,1 \t\t\t\t<dt>Description: \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[auto-assign]</strong> will auto-assign the creator of the item if set to 1, or will set the selection to the user who last modified the item if set to 2, or will give the choice between all the users for other values; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[email_notify]</strong> will send an email to the assigned user when the item is saved; \t\t\t\t<dd>multiple options must appear in the order specified, separated by commas. \t\t\t\t</dl>",
"group selector" => "Gruppenauswahl",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows a selection from a specified list of usergroups.\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>auto-assign</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Example: 1\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[auto-assign]</strong> will auto-assign the field to the usergroup of the creator if set to 1, or will set the selection to the group of the user who last modified the item if set to 2, or will give the choice between all the groups for other values;\n\t\t\t\t<dd>if the user does not have a default group set, the first group the user belongs to will be chosen, otherwise Registered group will be used.\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl> \t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows a selection from a specified list of usergroups. \t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>auto-assign</strong> \t\t\t\t<dt>Example: 1 \t\t\t\t<dt>Description: \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[auto-assign]</strong> will auto-assign the field to the usergroup of the creator if set to 1, or will set the selection to the group of the user who last modified the item if set to 2, or will give the choice between all the groups for other values; \t\t\t\t<dd>if the user does not have a default group set, the first group the user belongs to will be chosen, otherwise Registered group will be used. \t\t\t\t</dl>",
"IP selector" => "IP auswählen",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Provides a field for entering an IP address.\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>auto-assign</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Example: 1\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[auto-assign]</strong> will auto-populate the field with the IP address of the user who created the item if set to 1, or will set the field to the IP of the user who last modified the item if set to 2, or will be a free IP for other values.\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl> \t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Provides a field for entering an IP address. \t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>auto-assign</strong> \t\t\t\t<dt>Example: 1 \t\t\t\t<dt>Description: \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[auto-assign]</strong> will auto-populate the field with the IP address of the user who created the item if set to 1, or will set the field to the IP of the user who last modified the item if set to 2, or will be a free IP for other values. \t\t\t\t</dl>",
"page selector" => "Seitenauswahl",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows a selection from the list of pages.\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>auto-assign, size, create</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Example: 1\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[auto-assign]</strong> will auto-assign the creator of the item if set to 1\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[size]</strong> is the visible input length of the field in characters (<=0 not limited);\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[create]</strong> will create the page if not exits copy of the page with name value of this param.which pagename is the value of this param\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[link]</strong> will not display the link to the page if equals to n \n\t\t\t\t<dd>\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl> \t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows a selection from the list of pages. \t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>auto-assign, size, create</strong> \t\t\t\t<dt>Example: 1 \t\t\t\t<dt>Description: \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[auto-assign]</strong> will auto-assign the creator of the item if set to 1 \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[size]</strong> is the visible input length of the field in characters (<=0 not limited); \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[create]</strong> will create the page if not exits copy of the page with name value of this param.which pagename is the value of this param \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[link]</strong> will not display the link to the page if equals to n  \t\t\t\t<dd> \t\t\t\t</dl>",
"country selector" => "Länder auswählen",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows a selection from a specified list of countries.\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>name_flag,sort</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Example: 1,0\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[name_flag]</strong> default is 0 and will display both the country name and its flag, 1 will display only the country name, while 2 will show only the country flag;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[sortorder]</strong> specifies the order the country list should be displayed in, where 0 is the default and sorts according to the translated name, and 1 sorts according to the english name;\n\t\t\t\t<dd>if the country names are translated and option 1 is selected for the sort order, the countries will still appear translated, but will merely be in english order.\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl> \t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows a selection from a specified list of countries. \t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>name_flag,sort</strong> \t\t\t\t<dt>Example: 1,0 \t\t\t\t<dt>Description: \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[name_flag]</strong> default is 0 and will display both the country name and its flag, 1 will display only the country name, while 2 will show only the country flag; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[sortorder]</strong> specifies the order the country list should be displayed in, where 0 is the default and sorts according to the translated name, and 1 sorts according to the english name; \t\t\t\t<dd>if the country names are translated and option 1 is selected for the sort order, the countries will still appear translated, but will merely be in english order. \t\t\t\t</dl>",
"date and time" => "Datum und Zeit",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Provides drop-down options to accurately select a date and/or time.\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>datetime,startyear,endyear,blankdate</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Example: d,2000,,blank\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[datetime]</strong> will only allow a date to be selected if set to \"d\", and allows a full date and time selection if set to \"dt\", defaulting to \"dt\";\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[startyear]</strong> allows you to specify a custom first year in the date range (eg. 1987), default is current year;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[endyear]</strong> allows you to specify a custom end year in the date range (eg. 2020), default is 4 years from now;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[blankdate]</strong> when set to \"blank\" will default the initial date field to an empty date, and allow selection of empty dates;\n\t\t\t\t<dd>blankdate is overridden if the field isMandatory;\n\t\t\t\t<dd>when set to \"empty\" will allow selection of empty date but default to current date\n\t\t\t\t<dd>multiple options must appear in the order specified, separated by commas.\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Example: \"d,2000,2009,blank\"\n\t\t\t\t<dd>sets a date only field from 2000 through 2009, allowing blank dates.\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Funktion: Bietet eine Auswahlliste zu exakten Auswahl von Datum und/oder Zeit.\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Benutzung: <strong>DatumZeit,Startjahr,Endjahr,blank</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Beispiel: d,2000,,blank\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Beschreibung:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[DatumZeit]</strong> erlaubt nur Datumswahl, wenn \"d\" eingetragen wird und Datum und Zeit wenn \"dt\" eingetragen wird. Standard: \"dt\";\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[Startjahr]</strong> erlaubt die Angabe eines Jahres, bei dem die Auswahl anfangen soll (Beispiel: 1987). Standard ist das aktuelle Jahr;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[Endjahr]</strong> erlaubt die Angabe eines Jahres, bei dem die Auswahl enden soll (Beispiel: 2020). Standard: 4 Jahre von heute an;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[blank]</strong> Wenn \"blank\" angegeben wird, dann wird das anfängliche Datum zu einem leeren Datum und erlaubt die Auswahl von leeren Daten;\n\t\t\t\t<dd>blank wird überschrieben, wenn das Feld zwingend ist;\n\t\t\t\t<dd>wenn \"empty\" eingetragen wird, dann ist die Eingabe von leeren Daten erlaubt, standardmäßig wird aber das gegenwärtige Datum gewählt\n\t\t\t\t<dd>Multiple Optionen müssen in angegebener Reihenfolge erscheinen, getrennt durch Kommata.\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Beispiel: \"d,2000,2009,blank\"\n\t\t\t\t<dd>gibt den Datumsbereich zwischen 2000 - 2009 an und erlaubt leere Daten.\n\t\t\t\t</dl>",
"jscalendar" => "JS Kalender",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Provides a javascript graphical date selector to select a date and/or time.\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>datetime</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Example: dt\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[datetime]</strong> will only allow a date to be selected if set to \"d\", and allows a full date and time selection if set to \"dt\", defaulting to \"dt\".\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl> \t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Provides a javascript graphical date selector to select a date and/or time. \t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>datetime</strong> \t\t\t\t<dt>Example: dt \t\t\t\t<dt>Description: \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[datetime]</strong> will only allow a date to be selected if set to \"d\", and allows a full date and time selection if set to \"dt\", defaulting to \"dt\". \t\t\t\t</dl>",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows user to upload an image into the tracker item.\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>xListSize,yListSize,xDetailsSize,yDetailsSize,uploadLimitScale,shadowBox</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Example: 30,30,100,100,1000,item\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[xListSize]</strong> sets the pixel width of the image in the list view;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[yListSize]</strong> sets the pixel height of the image in the list view;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[xDetailSize]</strong> sets the pixel width of the image in the item view;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[yDetailSize]</strong> sets the pixel height of the image in the item view;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[uploadLimitScale]</strong> sets the maximum total size of the image, in pixels (width or height);\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[shadowbox]</strong> actives a shadowbox(if feature on) = \\'item\\': to use the same shadowbox for an item, =\\'individual\\': to use a shadowbox only for this image, other value= to set the group of images of the shadowbox ;\n\t\t\t\t<dd>images are stored in img/trackers;\n\t\t\t\t<dd>multiple options must appear in the order specified, separated by commas.\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Funktion: Erlaubt es dem Benutzer ein Bild in einen Trackereintrag hochzuladen.\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Benutzung: <strong>xListenGröße,yListenGröße,xDetailsGröße,yDetailsGröße,HochladeBegrenzung,shadowBox</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Beispiel: 30,30,100,100,1000,item\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Beschreibung:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[xListenGröße]</strong> legt die Breite des Bildes in der Listenansicht in Pixeln fest;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[yListenGröße]</strong> legt die Höhe des Bildes in der Listenansicht in Pixeln fest;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[xDetailGröße]</strong> legt die Breite des Bildes in der Einzelansicht in Pixeln fest;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[yDetailGröße]</strong> legt die Höhe des Bildes in der Einzelansicht in Pixeln fest;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[HochladeBegrenzung]</strong> legt die maximale Gesamtgröße des Bildes in Pixeln fest (Breite oder Höhe);\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[shadowbox]</strong> aktiviert eine Shadowbox (wenn die Funktion aktiviert) = \\'item\\': um die gleiche Shadowbox für einen Eintrag zu benutzen, =\\'individual\\': um die Shadowbox nur für dieses Bild zu benutzen, anderer Wert= um die Gruppe der Bilder der Shadowbox festzulegen ;\n\t\t\t\t<dd>Bilder werden in img/trackers gespeichert;\n\t\t\t\t<dd>Multiple Optionen müssen in der angegeben Reihefolge eingetragen werden, getrennt durch Kommata.\n\t\t\t\t</dl>",
"action" => "Aktion",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: ?\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>label,post,tiki-index.php,page:fieldname,highlight=test</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Example:\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[label]</strong> needs explanation;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[post]</strong> needs explanation;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[tiki-index.php]</strong> needs explanation;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[page:fieldname]</strong> needs explanation;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[highlight=test]</strong> needs explanation;\n\t\t\t\t<dd>multiple options must appear in the order specified, separated by commas.\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl> \t\t\t\t<dt>Function: ? \t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>label,post,tiki-index.php,page:fieldname,highlight=test</strong> \t\t\t\t<dt>Example: \t\t\t\t<dt>Description: \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[label]</strong> needs explanation; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[post]</strong> needs explanation; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[tiki-index.php]</strong> needs explanation; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[page:fieldname]</strong> needs explanation; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[highlight=test]</strong> needs explanation; \t\t\t\t<dd>multiple options must appear in the order specified, separated by commas. \t\t\t\t</dl>",
"header" => "Überschrift einfügen",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: will display the field name as a html header h2;\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>level,toggle</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Example: 2,o\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[level]</strong> level of the html header (default 2)\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[toggle]</strong> if \"o\" or \"c\" will toggle, \"c\" close by default, \"o\" open be default\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Funktion: zeigt den Feldnamen als HTML-Überschrift h2;\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Benutzung: <strong>Level,Umschalten</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Beispiel: 2,o\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Beschreibung:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[Level]</strong> Level der HTML-ÜBerschrift (Standard: 2)\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[Umschalten]</strong> \"o\" oder \"c\" erlaubt umschalten, \"c\" standardmäßig geschlossen, \"o\" standardmäßig offen\n\t\t\t\t</dl>",
"static text" => "Statischer Text",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows insertion of a static block of text into a tracker to augment input fields. (non-editable)\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>wikiparse,max</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Example: 1,20\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[wikiparse]</strong> will allow wiki syntax to be parsed if set to 1, otherwise default is 0 to only support line-breaks;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[max]</strong> is the maximum number of characters that are displayed in list mode;\n\t\t\t\t<dd>multiple options must appear in the order specified, separated by commas.\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl> \t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows insertion of a static block of text into a tracker to augment input fields. (non-editable) \t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>wikiparse,max</strong> \t\t\t\t<dt>Example: 1,20 \t\t\t\t<dt>Description: \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[wikiparse]</strong> will allow wiki syntax to be parsed if set to 1, otherwise default is 0 to only support line-breaks; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[max]</strong> is the maximum number of characters that are displayed in list mode; \t\t\t\t<dd>multiple options must appear in the order specified, separated by commas. \t\t\t\t</dl>",
"category" => "Kategorie",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows one or more categories under a main category to be assigned to the tracker item.\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>parentId,inputtype,selectall,descendants,help</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Example: 12,radio,1\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[parentId]</strong> is the ID of the main category, categories in the list will be children of this;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[inputtype]</strong> is one of [d|m|radio|checkbox], where d is a drop-down list, m is a multiple-selection drop-down list, radio and checkbox are self-explanatory;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[selectall]</strong> will provide a checkbox to automatically select all categories in the list if set to 1, default is 0;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[descendants]</strong> All descendant categories (not just first level children) will be included if set to 1, default is 0;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[help]</strong> will display the description in a popup in the input if set to 1, default is 0; only for checkbox or radio\n\t\t\t\t<dd>multiple options must appear in the order specified, separated by commas.\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl> \t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows one or more categories under a main category to be assigned to the tracker item. \t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>parentId,inputtype,selectall,descendants,help</strong> \t\t\t\t<dt>Example: 12,radio,1 \t\t\t\t<dt>Description: \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[parentId]</strong> is the ID of the main category, categories in the list will be children of this; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[inputtype]</strong> is one of [d|m|radio|checkbox], where d is a drop-down list, m is a multiple-selection drop-down list, radio and checkbox are self-explanatory; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[selectall]</strong> will provide a checkbox to automatically select all categories in the list if set to 1, default is 0; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[descendants]</strong> All descendant categories (not just first level children) will be included if set to 1, default is 0; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[help]</strong> will display the description in a popup in the input if set to 1, default is 0; only for checkbox or radio \t\t\t\t<dd>multiple options must appear in the order specified, separated by commas. \t\t\t\t</dl>",
"item link" => "Objektlink",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Provides a way to choose a value from another tracker (eventually with a link).\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>trackerId,fieldId,linkToItem,displayedFieldsList</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Example: 3,5,0,6|8,opc,PageName\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[trackerId]</strong> is the tracker ID of the fields you want to display;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[fieldId]</strong> is the field in [trackerId] from which you can select a value among all the field values of the items of [trackerId];\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[linkToItem]</strong> if set to 0 will simply display the value, but if set to 1 will provide a link directly to the item in the other tracker;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[displayedFieldsList]</strong> is a list of fields in [trackerId] to display instead of [fieldId], multiple fields can be separated with a |;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[status]</strong> filter on status (o, p, c, op, oc, pc or opc);\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[linkPage]</strong> is the name of the wiki page to link to with trackerlist plugin in it; \n\t\t\t\t<dd>multiple options must appear in the order specified, separated by commas.\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl> \t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Provides a way to choose a value from another tracker (eventually with a link). \t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>trackerId,fieldId,linkToItem,displayedFieldsList</strong> \t\t\t\t<dt>Example: 3,5,0,6|8,opc,PageName \t\t\t\t<dt>Description: \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[trackerId]</strong> is the tracker ID of the fields you want to display; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[fieldId]</strong> is the field in [trackerId] from which you can select a value among all the field values of the items of [trackerId]; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[linkToItem]</strong> if set to 0 will simply display the value, but if set to 1 will provide a link directly to the item in the other tracker; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[displayedFieldsList]</strong> is a list of fields in [trackerId] to display instead of [fieldId], multiple fields can be separated with a |; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[status]</strong> filter on status (o, p, c, op, oc, pc or opc); \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[linkPage]</strong> is the name of the wiki page to link to with trackerlist plugin in it;  \t\t\t\t<dd>multiple options must appear in the order specified, separated by commas. \t\t\t\t</dl>",
"items list" => "Objektliste",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Displays a list of field values from another tracker that has a relation with this tracker(eventually with a link).\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>trackerId,fieldIdThere,fieldIdHere,displayFieldIdThere,linkToItems</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Example: 5,3,4,10|11\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[trackerId]</strong> is the tracker ID of the fields you want to display;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[fieldIdThere]</strong> is the field (multiple fields can be separated with a \":\") you want to link with;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[fieldIdHere]</strong> is the field in this tracker you want to link with;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[displayFieldIdThere]</strong> the field(s) in [trackerId] you want to display, multiple fields can be separated by \"|\";\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[linkToItems]</strong> if set to 0 will simply display the value, but if set to 1 will provide a link directly to that values item in the other tracker;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[status]</strong> filter on status (o, p, c, op, oc, pc or opc);\n\t\t\t\t<dd>multiple options must appear in the order specified, separated by commas.\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl> \t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Displays a list of field values from another tracker that has a relation with this tracker(eventually with a link). \t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>trackerId,fieldIdThere,fieldIdHere,displayFieldIdThere,linkToItems</strong> \t\t\t\t<dt>Example: 5,3,4,10|11 \t\t\t\t<dt>Description: \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[trackerId]</strong> is the tracker ID of the fields you want to display; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[fieldIdThere]</strong> is the field (multiple fields can be separated with a \":\") you want to link with; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[fieldIdHere]</strong> is the field in this tracker you want to link with; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[displayFieldIdThere]</strong> the field(s) in [trackerId] you want to display, multiple fields can be separated by \"|\"; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[linkToItems]</strong> if set to 0 will simply display the value, but if set to 1 will provide a link directly to that values item in the other tracker; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[status]</strong> filter on status (o, p, c, op, oc, pc or opc); \t\t\t\t<dd>multiple options must appear in the order specified, separated by commas. \t\t\t\t</dl>",
"dynamic items list" => "Liste dynamischer Objekte",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Dynamically updates a selection list based on linked data from another tracker.\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>trackerId,filterFieldIdThere,filterFieldIdHere,listFieldIdThere,statusThere</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[trackerId]</strong> is the ID of the tracker to link with;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[filterFieldIdThere]</strong> is the field you want to link with in that tracker;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[filterFieldIdHere]</strong> is the field you want to link with in the current tracker;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[listFieldIdThere]</strong> is the field ID you wish to pull the selection list from, based on the value selected in fiterFieldIdHere matching field(s) in filterFieldIdThere;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[statusThere]</strong> restricts values appearing in the list to those coming from records in the other tracker that meet specified statuses of [o|p|c] or in combination (op, opc);\n\t\t\t\t<dd>multiple options must appear in the order specified, separated by commas.\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl> \t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Dynamically updates a selection list based on linked data from another tracker. \t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>trackerId,filterFieldIdThere,filterFieldIdHere,listFieldIdThere,statusThere</strong> \t\t\t\t<dt>Description: \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[trackerId]</strong> is the ID of the tracker to link with; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[filterFieldIdThere]</strong> is the field you want to link with in that tracker; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[filterFieldIdHere]</strong> is the field you want to link with in the current tracker; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[listFieldIdThere]</strong> is the field ID you wish to pull the selection list from, based on the value selected in fiterFieldIdHere matching field(s) in filterFieldIdThere; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[statusThere]</strong> restricts values appearing in the list to those coming from records in the other tracker that meet specified statuses of [o|p|c] or in combination (op, opc); \t\t\t\t<dd>multiple options must appear in the order specified, separated by commas. \t\t\t\t</dl>",
"email" => "Email",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows users to enter an email address with option of making it active.\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>link,watchopen,watchpending,watchclosed</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Example: 0,o\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[link]</strong> may be one of [0|1|2] and specifies how to display the email address, defaulting to 0 as plain text, 1 as an encoded hex mailto link, or 2 as a standard mailto link;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[watchopen]</strong> if set to \"o\" will email the address every time the status of the item changes to open;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[watchpending]</strong> if set to \"p\" will email the address every time the status of the item changes to pending;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[watchclosed]</strong> if set to \"c\" will email the address every time the status of the item changes to closed;\n\t\t\t\t<dd>multiple options must appear in the order specified, separated by commas.\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl> \t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows users to enter an email address with option of making it active. \t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>link,watchopen,watchpending,watchclosed</strong> \t\t\t\t<dt>Example: 0,o \t\t\t\t<dt>Description: \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[link]</strong> may be one of [0|1|2] and specifies how to display the email address, defaulting to 0 as plain text, 1 as an encoded hex mailto link, or 2 as a standard mailto link; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[watchopen]</strong> if set to \"o\" will email the address every time the status of the item changes to open; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[watchpending]</strong> if set to \"p\" will email the address every time the status of the item changes to pending; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[watchclosed]</strong> if set to \"c\" will email the address every time the status of the item changes to closed; \t\t\t\t<dd>multiple options must appear in the order specified, separated by commas. \t\t\t\t</dl>",
"url" => "URL",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows users to enter an url in a wiki syntax.\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl> \t\t\t\t<dt>Funktion: Erlaubt es Benutzern eine URL im Wikisyntax einzutragen. \t\t\t\t</dl>",
"auto-increment" => "Autovervollständigen",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows an incrementing value field, or itemId field. (non-editable)\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>start,prepend,append,itemId</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Example: 1,,,itemId\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[start]</strong> is the starting value for the field, defaults to 1;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[prepend]</strong> is text that will be displayed before the field;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[append]</strong> is text that will be displayed after the field;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[itemId]</strong> if set to \"itemId\" will set this field to match the value of the actual database itemId field value;\n\t\t\t\t<dd>multiple options must appear in the order specified, separated by commas.\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl> \t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows an incrementing value field, or itemId field. (non-editable) \t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>start,prepend,append,itemId</strong> \t\t\t\t<dt>Example: 1,,,itemId \t\t\t\t<dt>Description: \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[start]</strong> is the starting value for the field, defaults to 1; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[prepend]</strong> is text that will be displayed before the field; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[append]</strong> is text that will be displayed after the field; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[itemId]</strong> if set to \"itemId\" will set this field to match the value of the actual database itemId field value; \t\t\t\t<dd>multiple options must appear in the order specified, separated by commas. \t\t\t\t</dl>",
"user subscription" => "Benutzer",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allow registered users to subscribe themselves to a tracker item (think Evite.com).\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd>Use this field as you would to have people sign up for an event. It is best if the tracker is only editable by its creator or the admin.  To set the max number of subscribers, edit the tracker item and put the number at the beginning of the field.\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Example:\n\t\t\t\t<dd>Old field may have \"#\" or \"#2[0]\" in it.  Making it \"20#2[0]\" will set the max number to 20.\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl> \t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allow registered users to subscribe themselves to a tracker item (think Evite.com). \t\t\t\t<dt>Description: \t\t\t\t<dd>Use this field as you would to have people sign up for an event. It is best if the tracker is only editable by its creator or the admin.  To set the max number of subscribers, edit the tracker item and put the number at the beginning of the field. \t\t\t\t<dt>Example: \t\t\t\t<dd>Old field may have \"#\" or \"#2[0]\" in it.  Making it \"20#2[0]\" will set the max number to 20. \t\t\t\t</dl>",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Use Google Maps.\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Will display a Google Maps around a point.\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>use_as_item_location,bubble_fieldId,icon</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Example: y,23|24,img/icons2/icn_members.gif\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[use_as_item_location]</strong> if set to y, this google map field will be used as item location and object geo attributes are set when field value is changed.\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[bubble_fieldid]</strong> is the fieldId(s) (separated by |) that contains the text that will be displayed in the bubble of the map marker. The first field will be used as the link.\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[icon]</strong> is the url of the default icon to use for markers of items on the map.\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl> \t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Use Google Maps. \t\t\t\t<dt>Will display a Google Maps around a point. \t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>use_as_item_location,bubble_fieldId,icon</strong> \t\t\t\t<dt>Example: y,23|24,img/icons2/icn_members.gif \t\t\t\t<dt>Description: \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[use_as_item_location]</strong> if set to y, this google map field will be used as item location and object geo attributes are set when field value is changed. \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[bubble_fieldid]</strong> is the fieldId(s) (separated by |) that contains the text that will be displayed in the bubble of the map marker. The first field will be used as the link. \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[icon]</strong> is the url of the default icon to use for markers of items on the map. \t\t\t\t</dl>",
"system" => "System",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: System only.\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: None\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd>Needs a description.\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl> \t\t\t\t<dt>Funktion: nur System. \t\t\t\t<dt>Benutzung: keine \t\t\t\t<dt>Beschreibung: \t\t\t\t<dd>Benötigt einen Beschreibung. \t\t\t\t</dl>",
"computed field" => "Berechnetes Feld",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Provides a computed value based on numeric field values.\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>formula</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[formula]</strong> is the formula you wish to compute, using numeric values, operators \"+ - * / ( )\", and tracker fields identified with a leading #;\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Example: \"#3*(#4+5)\"\n\t\t\t\t<dd>adds the numeric value in item 4 by 5, and multiplies it by the numeric value in item 3.\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl> \t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Provides a computed value based on numeric field values. \t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>formula</strong> \t\t\t\t<dt>Description: \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[formula]</strong> is the formula you wish to compute, using numeric values, operators \"+ - * / ( )\", and tracker fields identified with a leading #; \t\t\t\t<dt>Example: \"#3*(#4+5)\" \t\t\t\t<dd>adds the numeric value in item 4 by 5, and multiplies it by the numeric value in item 3. \t\t\t\t</dl>",
"user preference" => "Benutzer",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows user preference changes from a tracker.\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>type</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Example: password\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[type]</strong> if value is password, will allow to change the user password, if value is email, will display/allow to change the user email, other values possible: language;\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl> \t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows user preference changes from a tracker. \t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>type</strong> \t\t\t\t<dt>Example: password \t\t\t\t<dt>Description: \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[type]</strong> if value is password, will allow to change the user password, if value is email, will display/allow to change the user email, other values possible: language; \t\t\t\t</dl>",
"user groups" => "Benutzergruppen",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows to display the user groups.\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl> \t\t\t\t<dt>Funktion: Erlaubt es Benutzergruppen anzuzeigen. \t\t\t\t</dl>",
"attachment" => "Anhang",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows a file to be attached to the tracker item.\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>listview</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Example: nu\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[listview]</strong> may be one of [n|t|s|u|m] on their own or in any combination (n, t, ns, nts), allowing you to see the attachment in the item list view as its name (n), its type (t), its size (n), the username of the uploader (u), or the mediaplayer plugin(m);\n\t\t\t\tnote that this option will cost an extra query to the database for each attachment and can severely impact performance with several attachments.\n\t\t\t\t<dd>\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl> \t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows a file to be attached to the tracker item. \t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>listview</strong> \t\t\t\t<dt>Example: nu \t\t\t\t<dt>Description: \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[listview]</strong> may be one of [n|t|s|u|m] on their own or in any combination (n, t, ns, nts), allowing you to see the attachment in the item list view as its name (n), its type (t), its size (n), the username of the uploader (u), or the mediaplayer plugin(m); \t\t\t\tnote that this option will cost an extra query to the database for each attachment and can severely impact performance with several attachments. \t\t\t\t<dd> \t\t\t\t</dl>",
"freetags" => "Freetags",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows freetags to be shown or added for tracker item\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>size</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Example: 80,n,n\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[size]</strong> is the visible length of the field in characters;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[hidehelp]</strong> if y, do not show help text when entering tags;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[hidesuggest]</strong> if y, do not show suggested tags when entering tags;  \n\t\t\t\t<dd>multiple options must appear in the order specified, separated by commas.\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl> \t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows freetags to be shown or added for tracker item \t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>size</strong> \t\t\t\t<dt>Example: 80,n,n \t\t\t\t<dt>Description: \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[size]</strong> is the visible length of the field in characters; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[hidehelp]</strong> if y, do not show help text when entering tags; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[hidesuggest]</strong> if y, do not show suggested tags when entering tags;   \t\t\t\t<dd>multiple options must appear in the order specified, separated by commas. \t\t\t\t</dl>",
"in group" => "in Gruppe",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows to display if a item user is in a group and when he was assigned to the group (needs a user selector field)\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>groupName,date</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Example: Members,date\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>GroupName</strong> Group to test. <strong>date</strong> displays the date the user was assigned in the group (if known), otherwise will display yes/no.\n\t\t\t\t<dd>\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl> \t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows to display if a item user is in a group and when he was assigned to the group (needs a user selector field) \t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>groupName,date</strong> \t\t\t\t<dt>Example: Members,date \t\t\t\t<dt>Description: \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>GroupName</strong> Group to test. <strong>date</strong> displays the date the user was assigned in the group (if known), otherwise will display yes/no. \t\t\t\t<dd> \t\t\t\t</dl>",
"stars" => "Sterne",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Display stars\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>list options (positive increasing numbers</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Example: 1,2,3,4\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd>Like the rating\n\t\t\t\t<dd>\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl> \t\t\t\t<dt>Funktion: zeigt Sterne an \t\t\t\t<dt>Benutzung: <strong>Listenoptionen (positive ansteigende Zahlen</strong> \t\t\t\t<dt>Beispiel: 1,2,3,4 \t\t\t\t<dt>Beschreibung: \t\t\t\t<dd>Wie bei der Bewertungsfunktion \t\t\t\t<dd> \t\t\t\t</dl>",
